INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', [' Code ЁЊ https://tinyurl.com/3c3vx2zn Video ЁЊ https://tinyurl.com/yc42pj55 1 Introduction Artificial intelligence is increasingly used in digital edu- cation to improve personalization and engagement. How- ever,ver, most lecture-based platforms remain static: learn- ers watch videos passively, receive uniform quizzes, receive receive limited feedback. Such systems fail to adapt to in- dividual learners in real time, often leaving students either under-challenged or overwhelmed, both of which reduce motivation and retention. Addressing this gap is key for scal- able, equitable, and engaging learning environments. Existing adaptive learning approaches, such as pretests or rigid rule-based adjustments, capture only coarse measures of ability (Claned 2025; Hyperspace 2025). They struggle to keep learners consistently within their optimal ЁАlearning zoneЁБ where the material is neither too easy nor too difficult. We present the Personal Adaptive Learner (PAL) , a sys- tem that transforms lecture videos into interactive learning sessions. PAL integrates multimodal video analysis with an Copyright \xa9 2026, Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence (www.aaai.org). All rights reserved. adaptive question engine that periodically inserts multiple- choice questions during playback.'])
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('apply_packaged_translation', ' Code ЁЊ https://tinyurl.com/3c3vx2zn Video ЁЊ https://tinyurl.com/yc42pj55 1 Introduction Artificial intelligence is increasingly used in digital edu- cation to improve personalization and engagement. How- ever,ver, most lecture-based platforms remain static: learn- ers watch videos passively, receive uniform quizzes, receive receive limited feedback. Such systems fail to adapt to in- dividual learners in real time, often leaving students either under-challenged or overwhelmed, both of which reduce motivation and retention. Addressing this gap is key for scal- able, equitable, and engaging learning environments. Existing adaptive learning approaches, such as pretests or rigid rule-based adjustments, capture only coarse measures of ability (Claned 2025; Hyperspace 2025). They struggle to keep learners consistently within their optimal ЁАlearning zoneЁБ where the material is neither too easy nor too difficult. We present the Personal Adaptive Learner (PAL) , a sys- tem that transforms lecture videos into interactive learning sessions. PAL integrates multimodal video analysis with an Copyright \xa9 2026, Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence (www.aaai.org). All rights reserved. adaptive question engine that periodically inserts multiple- choice questions during playback.')
