INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', ['2 Video-to-Question Dataset Generation Given a lecture video V and transcript T = { ( t i , u i ) } n i =1 , PAL uses a four-stage pipeline to generate timestamped, difficulty-rated questions (Koppolu et al. 2025; Singh et al. 2025). Transcript Analyzer. Scans T for candidate points via linguistic cues (e.g., ЁАis defined asЁБ) or every N sentences (Garrison et al. 2006). Context Validator. At each point, extracts a frame, ap- plies OCR for slide text, and uses LLaVA-mini for visual description. These combine with transcript text into a con- text bundle (Abinaya et al. 2024). Question Generator. Produces Q-A pairs from con- text. Difficulty is heuristic-based: factual (Easy), conceptual (Medium), applied (Hard). Supports MCQs and lightweight LLM generation (Du and Cardie 2018; Liu et al. 2025a). Difficulty Rater. Labels difficulty via rules (ЁАwhat isЁБ Ёњ Easy, ЁАwhy/howЁБ Ёњ Medium, ЁАapply/predictЁБ Ёњ Hard), with LLM fallback. Master Pipeline. The integrated tri plus one pipeline outputs structured JSON ( q, a, d, t, c ) for adaptive learning, quizzes, and study aids. This modular design is lightweight, extensible, and en- sures contextual accuracy by combining speech, vision, and text. 3 Adaptive Difficulty via Hybrid RL Problem.'])
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('apply_packaged_translation', '2 Video-to-Question Dataset Generation Given a lecture video V and transcript T = { ( t i , u i ) } n i =1 , PAL uses a four-stage pipeline to generate timestamped, difficulty-rated questions (Koppolu et al. 2025; Singh et al. 2025). Transcript Analyzer. Scans T for candidate points via linguistic cues (e.g., ЁАis defined asЁБ) or every N sentences (Garrison et al. 2006). Context Validator. At each point, extracts a frame, ap- plies OCR for slide text, and uses LLaVA-mini for visual description. These combine with transcript text into a con- text bundle (Abinaya et al. 2024). Question Generator. Produces Q-A pairs from con- text. Difficulty is heuristic-based: factual (Easy), conceptual (Medium), applied (Hard). Supports MCQs and lightweight LLM generation (Du and Cardie 2018; Liu et al. 2025a). Difficulty Rater. Labels difficulty via rules (ЁАwhat isЁБ Ёњ Easy, ЁАwhy/howЁБ Ёњ Medium, ЁАapply/predictЁБ Ёњ Hard), with LLM fallback. Master Pipeline. The integrated tri plus one pipeline outputs structured JSON ( q, a, d, t, c ) for adaptive learning, quizzes, and study aids. This modular design is lightweight, extensible, and en- sures contextual accuracy by combining speech, vision, and text. 3 Adaptive Difficulty via Hybrid RL Problem.')
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('Splitting sentences using SBD Model: (en) MiniSBDSentencizer',)
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('sentences', ['2 Video-to-Question Dataset Generation', 'Given a lecture video V and transcript T = { ( t i , u i ) } n i =1 , PAL uses a four-stage pipeline to generate timestamped, difficulty-rated questions (Koppolu et al. 2025; Singh et al. 2025).', 'Transcript Analyzer.', 'Scans T for candidate points via linguistic cues (e.g., ЁАis defined asЁБ) or every N sentences (Garrison et al. 2006).', 'Context Validator.', 'At each point, extracts a frame, ap- plies OCR for slide text, and uses LLaVA-mini for visual description.', 'These combine with transcript text into a con- text bundle (Abinaya et al. 2024).', 'Question Generator.', 'Produces Q-A pairs from con- text.', 'Difficulty is heuristic-based: factual (Easy), conceptual (Medium), applied (Hard).', 'Supports MCQs and lightweight LLM generation (Du and Cardie 2018; Liu et al. 2025a).', 'Difficulty Rater.', 'Labels difficulty via rules (ЁАwhat isЁБ Ёњ Easy, ЁАwhy/howЁБ Ёњ Medium, ЁАapply/predictЁБ Ёњ Hard), with LLM fallback.', 'Master Pipeline.', 'The integrated tri plus one pipeline outputs structured JSON ( q, a, d, t, c ) for adaptive learning, quizzes, and study aids.', 'This modular design is lightweight, extensible, and en- sures contextual accuracy by combining speech, vision, and text.', '3 Adaptive Difficulty via Hybrid RL Problem.'])
