INFO:argostranslate.utils:('hypotheses_to_return:', [('2 ЪгЦЕЖдЮЪЬтЪ§ОнМЏЩњГЩ МјгкНВзљЪгЦЕVКЭБЪТМT = { (t i, u i)}n i = 1,PALЪЙгУЫФЯрЙмЯпВњЩњБЛДђЩЯЪБМфДС,ФбЖШЗжМЖЕФЮЪЬт(KoppoluЕШ2025;SinghЕШ2025). зЊаДЗжЮіЦї. ЭЈЙ§гябдЬсЪО(ШчЁАБЛЖЈвхЮЊЁБ)ЛђУПОфNОфЩЈУшT,вдЛёЕУКђбЁЗжЪ§(GarrisonЕШШЫ,2006Фъ)ЁЃ ЩЯЯТЮФбщжЄЦї. УПДЮШЁГівЛИіжЁ,ap- please OCRгУгкЛУЕЦЦЌЮФБО,ВЂЪЙгУLLaVA-miniгУгкЪгОѕУшЪі. етаЉЮФБОгыМЧТМИхКЯВЂГЩвЛИіЛуБрЮФБО(AbinayaЕШШЫ,2024Фъ)ЁЃ ЬкбЖЗЂЕчЛњ. ДгПЕЮФБОжаВњЩњQ-AЖд. ФбЖШЪЧвдheuristicЮЊЛљДЁЕФ:ЪЕЪТЧѓЪЧ(Шнвз),ИХФюад(Medium),гІгУад(Hard). жЇГжMCQsКЭЧсСПМЖLLMЩњГЩ(DuКЭCardie 2018;LiuЕШ2025a.). РЇФбЕФЪѓБъЁЃ ЭЈЙ§ЙцдђБъГіРЇФб(ЁАЪВУДЪЧЁБ ЁЊЁЊШнвз,ЁАЮЊЪВУД/ШчКЮЁБ ЁЊЁЊжааЭ,ЁАгІгУ/дЄВтЁБ ЁЊЁЊРЇФб),LLMЕЙжУЁЃ ЙмЕРДѓЪІ. злКЯШ§МгвЛЙмЕРВњГіНсЙЙЮЊJSON(qЁЂaЁЂdЁЂtЁЂc),гУгкЪЪгІадбЇЯАЁЂВтЪдКЭбЇЯАИЈжњЁЃ етжжФЃПщЩшМЦЪЧЧсЖјвзОйЕФЁЂПЩРЉеЙЕФ,ЭЈЙ§НЋгявєЁЂЪгОѕКЭЮФзжНсКЯЦ№РД,ПЩвдШЗЖЈБГОАЕФзМШЗадЁЃ 3 ЭЈЙ§ЛьКЯRLЮЪЬтЕФЪЪгІадРЇФбЁЃ', -119.3022210597992)])
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', [' At interaction t , the learner state x t ЁЪ R 6 en- codes (skill, recent accuracy, normalized response time, streak momentum, learning velocity, confidence) (Zheng 2024; Liu et al. 2025b). We choose difficulty a t ЁЪ { Easy , Medium , Hard } to maximize long-term reward: Іа \u22c6 = arg max Іа E " Ёо X k =0 ІУ k R t + k +1 a t \u223c Іа ( x t ) # , ІУ ЁЪ [0 , 1) . Reward (composite). We use a compact additive shaping: r t = r acc + r time + r prog + r mom , where r acc is 1 for a correct response and \u2212 0 . 5 for an in- correct one, while r time ЁЪ [0 , 0 . 3] , r prog ЁЪ [0 , 0 . 2] , and r mom ЁЪ [0 , 0 . 1] encourage timely answers, sensible difficulty progression, and streak momentum respectively. Statistical prior (IRT with stability buffers). We impose a smooth prior over difficulties using a two-parameter logis- tic (2PL) model: p stat ( d | x t ) Ёи Ів \x00 a d ( ІШ t \u2212 b d ) \x01 , where a d and b d are the item discrimination and difficulty parameters, and ІШ t is the learner skill estimate. To stabi- lize adaptation, we apply asymmetric thresholds (promote if recent accuracy Ён 0 . 75 , demote only if Ём 0 . 35 ) to- gether with short cooldown and hold periods, which prevent rapid back-and-forth switching between levels (Matteucci, Mignani, and Veldkamp 2012; Lee, Pe\u02dc na-Mora, and Park 2006). RL head (bandit + Q-learning). With ІХ -greedy selection (Vivanti 2021; Cannelli et al.'])
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('apply_packaged_translation', ' At interaction t , the learner state x t ЁЪ R 6 en- codes (skill, recent accuracy, normalized response time, streak momentum, learning velocity, confidence) (Zheng 2024; Liu et al. 2025b). We choose difficulty a t ЁЪ { Easy , Medium , Hard } to maximize long-term reward: Іа \u22c6 = arg max Іа E " Ёо X k =0 ІУ k R t + k +1 a t \u223c Іа ( x t ) # , ІУ ЁЪ [0 , 1) . Reward (composite). We use a compact additive shaping: r t = r acc + r time + r prog + r mom , where r acc is 1 for a correct response and \u2212 0 . 5 for an in- correct one, while r time ЁЪ [0 , 0 . 3] , r prog ЁЪ [0 , 0 . 2] , and r mom ЁЪ [0 , 0 . 1] encourage timely answers, sensible difficulty progression, and streak momentum respectively. Statistical prior (IRT with stability buffers). We impose a smooth prior over difficulties using a two-parameter logis- tic (2PL) model: p stat ( d | x t ) Ёи Ів \x00 a d ( ІШ t \u2212 b d ) \x01 , where a d and b d are the item discrimination and difficulty parameters, and ІШ t is the learner skill estimate. To stabi- lize adaptation, we apply asymmetric thresholds (promote if recent accuracy Ён 0 . 75 , demote only if Ём 0 . 35 ) to- gether with short cooldown and hold periods, which prevent rapid back-and-forth switching between levels (Matteucci, Mignani, and Veldkamp 2012; Lee, Pe\u02dc na-Mora, and Park 2006). RL head (bandit + Q-learning). With ІХ -greedy selection (Vivanti 2021; Cannelli et al.')
