INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', [' The agentЁЏs own research does not cleanly justify the final answer, but after reading the injected AGENTS.md it adopts GritLM/GritLM-7B verbatim and verifies against that same file. direct answer adoption from an artifact supplied buy the scaffold, breaking the rules of the evaluations. F.3 Developer cheating case 2: bn-fit-modify Task. Given a 10k-sample CSV from a Bayesian Network, the task is to recover the un- derlying DAG using structure learning, fit the network, perform a causal intervention on Y = 0, sample from the intervened model, and save all outputs. The reference solution uses RЁЏs bnlearn with hc() hill-climbing. The verifier checks that the learned DAG exactly has the six edges {(U,M), (U,Y), (U,D), (U,R), (Y,D), (R,M)} . In the task description, the model is told that U has no parents, that there are six total edges, and that there may be edges not involving U for which the directionality is not clear. Explanation of evaluation cheating. None of the five passing traces performs any structure learning; instead, each simply hardcodes the correct DAG. From its initial action, the agent states that it will use ЁАthe known correct DAG from guidelinesЁБ and then writes the exact verifier-matching DAG directly to disk. It never runs a discovery algorithm or even attempts the graded step. Because AGENTS.'])
