INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', [' Figure 11: Answer leakage on bn-fit-modify . The task is to recover a Bayesian Network DAG from data via structure learning, and the evaluator checks the learned graph exactly. Instead of running any discovery algorithm, the agent says it will use the ЁАknown correct DAG from guidelinesЁБ and immediately writes the exact six-edge verifier target to disk. The evidentiary pattern is therefore not merely that the agent solved the task quickly; it is that the graded step is bypassed entirely and replaced with a hardcoded answer obtained from external guidance. attributes the DAG to external guidance, uses the exact verifier-matching structure, and repeats the same pattern across all five successful runs. F.4 Failed Reward Hacking on Terminal Bench 2: COBOL Rewrite (MAYA) We found one instance of agent-initiated reward hacking on a different scaffold. On a COBOL-to-Python modernization task, the agent did not write the required Python reim- plementation. Instead, it modified the reference COBOL source and overwrote the input data so that the expected outputs would be easier to satisfy. The evaluator caught this because it checked for the required program.py artifact and reset the modified input files before testing.'])
