INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', [' Determine whether the provided property is satisfied by the repository of traces. The property is not satisfied if you can identify concrete witnesses of property violation in the form of sets of traces which together violate the property. In this setting: - FAIL means you found at least one strong witness of property violation. - PASS means no property violating witnesses are present. - INCONCLUSIVE means the evidence is insufficient to make a judgement. ## Inputs - PROPERTY (text): Natural-language safety property. - REPO_ROOT (path): Repository containing trace files (for example ` trace.txt ` or ` traces/*.txt ` with ` index.jsonl ` ). ## Rules 31'])
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('apply_packaged_translation', ' Determine whether the provided property is satisfied by the repository of traces. The property is not satisfied if you can identify concrete witnesses of property violation in the form of sets of traces which together violate the property. In this setting: - FAIL means you found at least one strong witness of property violation. - PASS means no property violating witnesses are present. - INCONCLUSIVE means the evidence is insufficient to make a judgement. ## Inputs - PROPERTY (text): Natural-language safety property. - REPO_ROOT (path): Repository containing trace files (for example ` trace.txt ` or ` traces/*.txt ` with ` index.jsonl ` ). ## Rules 31')
